```{r setup, include=FALSE}
knitr::opts_chunk$set(eval = T, echo = F, message = F, cache=F)

library(flexdashboard)
library(tidyverse)
library(plotly)
library(knitr)
library(maps)
library(usmap)

theme_set(theme_bw())
```

```{r data}
data(unemp)
unemp$colorBuckets <- as.numeric(cut(unemp$unemp, c(0, 2, 4, 6, 8, 10, 100)))
data(statepop)
```

# Unemployment Maps {data-orientation="rows"}

## Row 1

### US unemployment


```{r, all_US}
p <- plot_usmap(data = unemp, 
           values = "unemp",
           size = .05,
           theme = theme_minimal()) +
      theme(axis.title = element_blank(),
         axis.ticks = element_blank(),
         axis.text = element_blank()) +
   labs(fill = "Unemployment") +
   viridis::scale_fill_viridis()

ggplotly(p)
```

### Unemployment for CA

```{r, CA_only}
p <- plot_usmap(include = "CA", # show only CA
                data = unemp, 
           values = "unemp",
           size = .05,
           theme = theme_minimal()) +
      theme(axis.title = element_blank(),
         axis.ticks = element_blank(),
         axis.text = element_blank()) +
   labs(fill = "Unemployment") +
   viridis::scale_fill_viridis()

ggplotly(p)
```

# Population Maps 

## Row 2

### US Population 2015

```{r, population}
p <- plot_usmap(data = statepop, 
           values = "pop_2015") +
  scale_fill_continuous(low = "white", high = "red", 
                        name = "Population (2015)", 
                        label = scales::comma) + 
  theme(legend.position = "right")
ggplotly(p)
```
